# @purpose:      How is Lyrebird architected at a glance — its modules, external services, and users, and how they interact?
# @audience:     Engineers onboarding to Lyrebird (mid-level)
# @out-of-scope: Deployment/infra topology, DB table schemas, data-flow sequences, ADR references, build-order rationale, per-module feature lists
# @tier:         governed
# @source:       references/lyrebird_architecture.md

...@../../references/style

direction: down

# --- Users ---------------------------------------------------------------
researcher:  Researcher              { class: actor }
participant: Anonymous Participant   { class: actor }

# --- Feature modules -----------------------------------------------------
# Every module also depends on the foundation layer (platform + auth); those
# edges are elided by convention — see the foundation note below.
projects:     projects                { class: svc }
scripts:      scripts                 { class: svc }
runs:         runs                    { class: svc }
interview:    interview               { class: svc }
test_harness: test-harness            { class: svc }
evaluation:   evaluation              { class: svc }
analytics:    analytics               { class: svc }

# --- Foundation layer (everything sits on this) --------------------------
foundation: Foundation layer {
  class: group
  tooltip: Every feature module depends on platform + auth. Those edges are elided.
  platform: platform { class: svc }
  auth:     auth     { class: svc }
}

# --- External services ---------------------------------------------------
bedrock:    AWS Bedrock\n(Claude Haiku / Sonnet, ap-southeast-2) { class: external }
cilogon:    CILogon\n(OIDC)                                       { class: external }
ses:        AWS SES\n(notification email)                        { class: external }
cloudflare: Cloudflare\n(DNS · TLS · CDN · WAF · Tunnel)          { class: external }

# --- User interactions ---------------------------------------------------
researcher  -> cloudflare:  researcher surface
participant -> cloudflare:  participant surface
cloudflare  -> projects:    ingress (all HTTP)

# --- Researcher authoring chronology -------------------------------------
projects -> scripts:  scopes / owns scripts
scripts  -> runs:     run pins a published script version
runs     -> interview: session belongs to a run

# --- Quality + review ----------------------------------------------------
test_harness -> scripts:    evaluates published versions
interview    -> evaluation: real sessions reviewed
runs         -> evaluation: evaluation-mode flag

# --- Analytics / cost recording ------------------------------------------
interview    -> analytics: emits cost data        { class: weak }
test_harness -> analytics: emits cost data        { class: weak }
runs         -> analytics: per-project attribution { class: weak }

# --- External-service interactions ---------------------------------------
foundation.auth -> cilogon:  OIDC auth code flow   { class: weak }
interview    -> bedrock:  streamed LLM inference
test_harness -> bedrock:  LLM-to-LLM evaluation
interview    -> ses:      completion / withdrawal email { class: weak }

# --- Convention note -----------------------------------------------------
note: |md
  **Convention:** every feature module also
  depends on the **foundation layer**
  (`platform` + `auth`). Those per-module
  edges are elided for legibility; only the
  meaningful feature-to-feature, user, and
  external-service interactions are drawn.
  Dashed edges are async / cost / out-of-band.
| { class: group; near: bottom-center; width: 360 }
